Sentencas: Design of optimal microstructures for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) electrodes is a complicated task because of the multitude of electro-chemo-physical phenomena taking place simultaneously that directly affect working conditions (cell temperature, current density, and flow rates) of the SOFC electrode and therefore its performance.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: In this study, an innovative design paradigm is presented to obtain a part of geometry-related electrochemical and physical properties of an infiltrated SOFC electrode.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: A range of digitally realized microstructures with different backbone porosity and electrocatalyst particle loading under various deposition conditions are generated.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Triple phase boundary (TPB), active surface density of particles, and gas transport factor are evaluated in realized models on the basis of selected infiltration strategy.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: On the basis of this database, a neural network is trained to relate desired range of input geometric parameters to a property hull.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: The effect of backbone porosity, loading, distribution, and aggregation behavior of particles is systematically investigated on the performance indicators.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: It is shown that from the microstructures with very high amount of TPB and particle contact surface density, a relatively low gas diffusion factor should be expected; meanwhile, increasing those parameters does not have sensible contradiction with each other.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Excessive agglomerating of particles has a negative effect on TPB density, but the distribution of seeds always has a positive effect.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Direct search and genetic algorithm optimization techniques are used finally to achieve optimal microstructures on the basis of assumed target functions for effective geometric properties.
Titulo: Investigation of the geometric property hull for infiltrated solid oxide fuel cell electrodes
